data.aboutMe: I am a computer scientist, mathematician, logician, cryptanalyst, philosopher, mathematician and a long distance runner. I am considered a forefather of computer science and my work decrypting engima in World War II provided one of the single largest contributions to the allied victory.
I am a pioneer in the field of computer science. I invented one of the first high level programming languages and am credited with poularizing ther term debugging.
I am an English romantic fiction writer, known for my biting social commentary.
I am an inventor and business man. I invented the phonograph, the motion picture camera, and a practical light bulb.
